This article is a fact sheet on the federal support provided for the Flint water crisis in Michigan. The Obama administration has responded with an all-of-government approach, providing assistance in various areas such as water distribution, Medicaid expansion, funding for Head Start and local health centers, water testing, and support for the local economy. The federal government will continue to offer expertise and technical assistance for as long as needed. Some specific actions include providing water, filters, and cartridges; ensuring access to safe water in public housing; offering blood lead testing; investigating rashes and skin concerns; expanding Medicaid coverage for impacted individuals; providing guidance and funding for health services; improving nutrition assistance; offering behavioral health support; monitoring the restoration of the water system; providing economic recovery assistance; connecting the community to public health resources; and building capacity through national service programs.